sentences: Eddy Merle Watson (February 8, 1949 – October 23, 1985) was an American folk and bluegrass guitarist.
Merle played and recorded albums together with his father from age 15 until his death in a tractor accident 21 years later.
Watson died in a farm accident in 1985 at age 36.
